    :markdown
      As long as there are 'bad' and 'good' divs, anything can go inside, including divs and images

    pre.
      +exercise({name:'ch03-highlighters-e2'})        
        .progress-box
        +statement
          h4 Exercise:  Planets and satellites
          | Select which one of the following are a satellites in the Solar System
        +select-to-highlight
          .row.container
            .item.bad.col-md-3 Mercury
              +img('http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/88/Reprocessed_Mariner_10_image_of_Mercury.jpg')
            .item.good.col-md-3 Io
              +img('http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7b/Io_highest_resolution_true_color.jpg')
            .item.bad.col-md-3 Mars
              +img('http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/Mars_and_Syrtis_Major_-_GPN-2000-000923.jpg')
            .item.good.col-md-3 Phobos
              +img('http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5c/Phobos_colour_2008.jpg')
    p CSS:
    pre.
      .ch03-highlighters-e2 .row
        background-color: #000

      .ch03-highlighters-e2 .item
        color: #fff
        margin: 0
        padding: 5px 10px
        text-align: center

      .ch03-highlighters-e2 img
        opacity: .5

      .ch03-highlighters-e2 .item.good.selected img
        opacity: 1

      .ch03-highlighters-e2 .item.bad.selected img
        opacity: 0.3

